<br>
I haven't been in Befallen for ages (probably pre-Kunark, the more I think about it), so it may well have changed.  It was an ok soloing dungeon for the first floor... the skellies were generally easy and trains were not terrible.<br>
<br>
However, the 2nd floor could easily get out of hand if you weren't extremely careful.  Corpse runs were also difficult, since we don't get an invis vs. undead spell.  It was too easy to get pops behind you, and have no easy way to sprint for the zone.<br>
<br>
And god help you if there was a group lower down... people dashing for the zone and bringing the entire dungeon with them used to be common.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailurya@themagicianstower>Ailurya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#333333>(2/13/03 2:05:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Befallen?</span><hr size=1> Befallen used to be a good soloing zone up to 16-18 or so, or certainly my Monk, SK, Necro and Rogue spent much of their time from level 8 to 18 there. The problem is that they upped the levels of the skellies near the entrance so you can't get in easily at low levels, and they added far more Necros who'll heal the mobs you're fighting even if they're green.<br>
<br>
For a duo or small group it should still be pretty good, but breaking the entrance at low level may be tricky (three skellies in aggro range so you can't single pull), and you'll need to pull the mobs away from any nearby necros to avoid heals.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Corpse runs were also difficult, since we don't get an invis vs. undead spell.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Doesn't normal invis work for most of the mobs in the dungeon? I'm sure my Necro was running around in there at times with Gather Shadows rather than invis vs undead; though, of course, a Necro doesn't have to worry much about corpse runs from 12-35 when they can summon their corpse for less than 2pp.<br>
<br>
